Foreword:
Dragon2 is an independent CUDA / C++ implementation of the paper by
Guermond et al. On the implementation of a robust and efficient finite element-based parallel solver for the compressible Navier–Stokes equations,
and is inspired by the ryujin project
(https://github.com/conservation-laws/ryujin), which is licensed under the
Apache License 2.0 with LLVM Exception. Please refer to ryujin repository for
its authors and license.

